  <compounddef id="SPRITELOAD" kind="page">
    <compoundname>SPRITELOAD</compoundname>
    <title>SPRITELOAD Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">SPRITELOAD<sp/>integer-variable,<sp/>string-expression</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Loads an image from disk as a <bold>sprite</bold> and stores its <bold>handle</bold> in the given integer variable. <linebreak/>
 Use the handle with <ref refid="PLOT" kindref="compound">PLOT</ref> or <ref refid="PLOTQUAD" kindref="compound">PLOTQUAD</ref>, and free it with <ref refid="SPRITEFREE" kindref="compound">SPRITEFREE</ref> when finished.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The <bold>first argument must be an integer variable</bold>, not a literal or expression. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Paths are <bold>case-insensitive</bold> and <computeroutput>.</computeroutput> / <computeroutput>..</computeroutput> are <bold>not supported</bold> in paths.</para>
</simplesect>
<hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="SPRITELOAD_1autotoc_md502">
<title>Supported formats</title>
<para><table rows="8" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes" align='right'><para>Extension   </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>File type    </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no" align='right'><para><computeroutput>JPG</computeroutput>   </para>
